Just relax.

499
00:32:22,253 --> 00:32:24,233
Until the memories come.

500
00:33:01,885 --> 00:33:02,799
<i>What?</i>

501
00:33:05,568 --> 00:33:07,642
<i>I wish you were standing
behind the eight ball</i>

502
00:33:07,767 --> 00:33:09,653
<i>when I came crashing through.</i>

503
00:33:11,254 --> 00:33:12,654
<i>Go to hell, Lloyd.</i>

504
00:33:18,123 --> 00:33:19,383
What did you see?

505
00:33:20,266 --> 00:33:21,630
I was on the phone.

506
00:33:27,172 --> 00:33:28,898
Do you know who you were talking to?

507
00:33:31,834 --> 00:33:32,984
Lloyd Simcoe.

508
00:33:52,611 --> 00:33:54,211
You dropped something.

509
00:33:55,866 --> 00:33:57,345
Let's start again.

510
00:33:57,470 --> 00:34:01,240
You were conducting an experiment
in plasma-wakefield acceleration.

511
00:34:01,464 --> 00:34:03,233
Am I correct in that assumption?

512
00:34:05,373 --> 00:34:08,379
I thought I made it clear,
I can't tell you.

513
00:34:11,808 --> 00:34:13,425
Get the...
Lloyd!

514
00:34:13,770 --> 00:34:15,427
Were you successful, Dr. Simcoe?

515
00:34:17,027 --> 00:34:18,013
All right.

516
00:34:18,181 --> 00:34:20,241
Did your facility detect
anything superluminal?

517
00:34:20,366 --> 00:34:22,368
This has nothing to do with simon.
Why?

518
00:34:22,644 --> 00:34:24,450
Was there any Cherenkov radiation?

519
00:34:30,814 --> 00:34:31,814
I can't.

520
00:34:36,139 --> 00:34:37,239
Lloyd! Help!

521
00:34:37,904 --> 00:34:39,076
Very well then.

522
00:34:39,245 --> 00:34:42,577
Let the wild rumpus begin.

523
00:34:52,021 --> 00:34:53,090
Hey, kdo.

524
00:34:53,906 --> 00:34:56,083
Go back to sleep, babe.
I was checking in on you.

525
00:34:56,208 --> 00:34:57,142
I can't.

526
00:34:57,530 --> 00:34:59,096
Will you sing some more?

527
00:35:01,011 --> 00:35:02,808
I think I exhausted my repertoire.

528
00:35:03,936 --> 00:35:05,336
I have to go home.

529
00:35:05,597 --> 00:35:07,697
I saved you this from my dinner.

530
00:35:09,636 --> 00:35:11,485
A cookie? You did?

531
00:35:17,780 --> 00:35:18,780
Thank you.

532
00:35:25,471 --> 00:35:26,885
Hey, Aaron. It's Mark.

533
00:35:27,010 --> 00:35:29,010
I think I could use some help.

534
00:36:20,345 --> 00:36:21,645
Talk to me, man.

535
00:36:23,384 --> 00:36:24,776
What's happened, Mark?

536
00:36:24,901 --> 00:36:27,507
Why are you sitting here in your car
in front of a bar?

537
00:36:28,108 --> 00:36:29,478
It's what's gonna happen.

538
00:36:32,144 --> 00:36:33,394
My therapist...

539
00:36:34,651 --> 00:36:36,133
gave me this drug...

540
00:36:37,988 --> 00:36:41,558
to unlock the parts of my flash-forward
I couldn't remember

541
00:36:41,683 --> 00:36:42,908
because I was drinking.

542
00:36:46,153 --> 00:36:48,056
<i>It's me.
I need to talk to you.</i>

543
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:50,508
<i>This isn't a good time.</i>

544
00:36:50,633 --> 00:36:52,053
I was on the phone,

545
00:36:52,550 --> 00:36:53,919
with Lloyd Simcoe.

546
00:36:55,953 --> 00:36:58,423
<i>- Have you been drinking?
- Go to hell, Lloyd.</i>

547
00:36:58,591 --> 00:37:00,485
I told him
I didn't want to talk to him.

548
00:37:00,610 --> 00:37:03,137
<i>- You have right to hate me, but...
- I don't hate you.</i>

549
00:37:03,346 --> 00:37:06,473
I wish you were behind the eight ball
when I came crashing through.

550
00:37:06,641 --> 00:37:08,517
<i>Fine, but we need to talk
about the Q.E.D.</i>

551
00:37:09,143 --> 00:37:10,965
<i>Sounded like
we were working together.</i>

552
00:37:11,090 --> 00:37:14,356
<i>I'm not sure. It's highly theoretical
but I'm close to cracking it.</i>

553
00:37:14,567 --> 00:37:16,398
<i>Listen to me.
Close is not good enough.</i>

554
00:37:16,523 --> 00:37:19,653
<i>- D. Gibbons told me about...
- D. Gibbons lied to you.</i>

555
00:37:21,710 --> 00:37:24,575
<i>We're running out of time
unless we can stop this...</i>

556
00:37:25,536 --> 00:37:26,910
And then I told him...

557
00:37:30,817 --> 00:37:32,541
<i>There's gonna be another blackout.</i>

558
00:37:41,244 --> 00:37:43,093
- Are you sure?
- I'm positive.

559
00:37:43,632 --> 00:37:45,679
There's gonna be another blackout.

560
00:37:45,847 --> 00:37:47,890
If Simcoe saw the same thing
you did,

561
00:37:48,058 --> 00:37:49,999
Why's he been sitting
on this Information?

562
00:37:50,124 --> 00:37:52,352
- Why hasn't he come forward?
- I don't know.

563
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:54,060
Let's find him and ask him.

564
00:37:54,581 --> 00:37:55,798
Let me back in,

565
00:37:55,923 --> 00:37:57,192
and I can track him.

566
00:37:57,317 --> 00:37:58,598
Look, go home.

567
00:37:58,894 --> 00:38:01,606
I'm doing my best to get you reinstated.
I promise.

568
00:38:01,905 --> 00:38:04,938
- What am I supposed to do till then?
- You said you saw more clues,

569
00:38:05,063 --> 00:38:06,199
from your vision.

570
00:38:07,443 --> 00:38:08,335
Work them...

571
00:38:08,460 --> 00:38:10,502
- But be quiet about it.
- All right.

572
00:38:11,156 --> 00:38:13,146
This business
about another blackout...

573
00:38:13,573 --> 00:38:14,946
Keep it to yourself.

574
00:38:15,235 --> 00:38:18,295
If we can't tell the world
when it's going to happen,

575
00:38:18,463 --> 00:38:20,363
That's beyond irresponsible.

576
00:38:22,342 --> 00:38:24,554
This is the number
for one of our missing E.M.T.S.

577
00:38:24,679 --> 00:38:27,346
We're hoping the phone might
still be in the ambulance.

578
00:38:27,514 --> 00:38:28,602
Can you track it?

579
00:38:28,727 --> 00:38:30,958
If the battery's got juice,
I can capture the signal

580
00:38:31,083 --> 00:38:32,893
and triangulate its position.

581
00:38:33,061 --> 00:38:36,104
- How close can you get us?
- To within 50 m, if it's in the city.

582
00:38:36,272 --> 00:38:37,272
Let's do it.

583
00:38:48,076 --> 00:38:50,535
I made it for you, daddy,
To cheer you up.

584
00:38:51,769 --> 00:38:52,769
It worked.

585
00:38:53,960 --> 00:38:55,352
Thank you, it's beautiful.

586
00:38:55,477 --> 00:38:56,777
What's all this?

587
00:38:57,293 --> 00:38:58,956
It's a giant puzzle,

588
00:39:00,006 --> 00:39:02,128
Something I still haven't
figured out yet.

589
00:39:02,837 --> 00:39:04,591
When I do jigsaw puzzles
at Nana's house,

590
00:39:05,461 --> 00:39:09,040
I always feel that way when she dumps
the pieces out on the table.

591
00:39:10,704 --> 00:39:13,704
But we always start
with the corners and work in.

592
00:39:14,484 --> 00:39:16,507
At least you know what they are.

593
00:39:16,714 --> 00:39:18,364
Start with the corners.

594
00:39:19,571 --> 00:39:20,571
Come here.

595
00:39:23,736 --> 00:39:26,971
Sometimes we feel God's hand
on the back of our neck,

596
00:39:27,262 --> 00:39:29,074
pushing us towards something.</i>

597
00:39:29,879 --> 00:39:31,254
And sometimes,

598
00:39:31,705 --> 00:39:33,286
we feel totally abandoned.

599
00:39:34,477 --> 00:39:35,677
That's normal.

600
00:39:35,985 --> 00:39:38,208
But just because
you don't feel something,

601
00:39:38,376 --> 00:39:40,276
doesn't mean it's not there.

602
00:39:43,723 --> 00:39:46,894
How many people here
have gotten sunburned on a cloudy day?

603
00:39:47,969 --> 00:39:50,220
You didn't think
it was working on you,

604
00:39:50,722 --> 00:39:51,847
but it was.

605
00:39:52,348 --> 00:39:54,398
God's love is just like that...

606
00:39:55,300 --> 00:39:56,643
Working for your good,

607
00:39:57,159 --> 00:39:59,188
whether you are aware of it or not.

608
00:40:02,150 --> 00:40:03,066
Here you go.

609
00:40:03,234 --> 00:40:04,234
Thank you.

610
00:40:06,336 --> 00:40:07,195
Sorry.

611
00:40:07,363 --> 00:40:09,513
- I just had a question.
- Sure.

612
00:40:09,967 --> 00:40:12,075
What about our responsibility
before God?

613
00:40:12,936 --> 00:40:14,995
- Don't we owe him something?
- Like what?

614
00:40:15,344 --> 00:40:16,344
Obedience?

615
00:40:18,172 --> 00:40:20,167
We need to follow the rules
that he sets out.

616
00:40:21,293 --> 00:40:22,475
And if we don't?

617
00:40:23,134 --> 00:40:24,434
We get punished.

618
00:40:25,731 --> 00:40:29,259
I just don't see how you can say
that the blackout was good.

619
00:40:29,641 --> 00:40:32,637
And look at all the people that died.
Look at all the trouble it's causing.

620
00:40:33,077 --> 00:40:35,419
- Clearly, I've upset you.
- Don't you think...

621
00:40:35,725 --> 00:40:36,847
In the very least,

622
00:40:36,972 --> 00:40:40,082
the flash-forwards
were a wake-up call for us

623
00:40:40,937 --> 00:40:43,459
to get our act together
before it's too late?

624
00:40:43,584 --> 00:40:45,609
- I didn't catch your name.
- Nicole.

625
00:40:46,059 --> 00:40:47,319
My name is Timothy.

626
00:40:47,584 --> 00:40:49,279
I'd really like to keep talking,

627
00:40:49,447 --> 00:40:52,282
but if I don't get out of here
before my hour's up, I get charged.

628
00:40:52,957 --> 00:40:56,036
- We, thanks.
- There's a coffee shop I like nearby.

629
00:40:56,204 --> 00:40:58,904
If you want to talk
about it again later...

630
00:41:12,652 --> 00:41:16,043
Red Panda provides humanitarian aid
all around the world.

631
00:41:16,168 --> 00:41:18,825
Everything from micro-investments
to education.

632
00:41:19,287 --> 00:41:22,604
We've been busy since the blackout.
I'm sure you can imagine.

633
00:41:22,880 --> 00:41:24,973
You said you do work
all over the world.

634
00:41:25,951 --> 00:41:27,985
We grew out of D.H.S. in the '90s,

635
00:41:28,332 --> 00:41:30,432
Demographic and health services.

636
00:41:30,557 --> 00:41:32,531
We're in South America,
the Middle East,

637
00:41:32,950 --> 00:41:34,800
The African subcontinent...

638
00:41:35,066 --> 00:41:35,992
Somalia?

639
00:41:36,765 --> 00:41:38,742
Was Red Panda there in '91?

640
00:41:39,080 --> 00:41:41,130
There was no Red Panda In 1991.

641
00:41:41,540 --> 00:41:43,375
We weren't chartered Until '98.

642
00:41:43,568 --> 00:41:44,868
And you send in,

643
00:41:45,225 --> 00:41:47,879
- Teams of people?
- With clean water supplies, mostly.

644
00:41:48,497 --> 00:41:52,259
The warlords keep most everyone out,
But, humanitarian groups can get in.

645
00:41:52,510 --> 00:41:55,672
Is there anyone
I could talk to about, maybe...

646
00:41:57,396 --> 00:41:59,946
Piggybacking
on one of red panda's trips?

647
00:42:01,024 --> 00:42:02,024
Doubt it.

648
00:42:02,519 --> 00:42:03,812
Not to be disrespectful,

649
00:42:03,980 --> 00:42:06,022
but most of the people working here

650
00:42:06,190 --> 00:42:09,068
probably have police records
as thick as the bible.

651
00:42:09,193 --> 00:42:10,801
We're not like that anymore.

652
00:42:11,647 --> 00:42:13,697
Have a nice day, agent Benford.

653
00:42:16,606 --> 00:42:19,877
- You have to let me pay your coffee.
- It's okay.

654
00:42:20,446 --> 00:42:22,319
I didn't have any plans anyway.

655
00:42:25,394 --> 00:42:27,120
It's not like
he's scary or anything.

656
00:42:27,394 --> 00:42:30,226
- I feel better if you're here.
- I'll be right here if you need me.

657
00:42:30,897 --> 00:42:31,797
Great.

658
00:42:32,387 --> 00:42:34,750
Can you see
if you can get the change in pennies?

659
00:42:41,993 --> 00:42:44,227
Can I buy you a cup of coffee?

660
00:42:44,850 --> 00:42:47,139
That's all right.
I'm getting one to go.

661
00:42:49,273 --> 00:42:52,152
Why don't you tell me
what upset you earlier?

662
00:42:56,050 --> 00:42:57,550
In my flash-forward,

663
00:42:58,269 --> 00:42:59,493
I was underwater.

664
00:43:01,986 --> 00:43:03,371
Someone was drowning me.

665
00:43:05,291 --> 00:43:06,430
And in the end,

666
00:43:07,158 --> 00:43:08,208
I was dead.

667
00:43:09,667 --> 00:43:13,366
People ask me all the time
to interpret what they saw,

668
00:43:14,501 --> 00:43:15,425
And i can't.

669
00:43:16,330 --> 00:43:19,554
Ultimately,
interpretation is your responsibility.

670
00:43:19,860 --> 00:43:21,930
How could my drowning be good?

671
00:43:22,055 --> 00:43:23,850
What if you were being baptized?

672
00:43:24,148 --> 00:43:27,062
- Wouldn't that be a good thing?
- But then why was I struggling?

673
00:43:27,230 --> 00:43:29,391
I'm sorry to say
I've dropped more than one person

674
00:43:29,516 --> 00:43:31,149
in a full-immersion baptism...

675
00:43:31,613 --> 00:43:32,919
Water gets up their nose.

676
00:43:33,044 --> 00:43:35,278
- They freak out, slip away.
- But i died.

677
00:43:35,446 --> 00:43:36,321
Or fainted.

678
00:43:37,326 --> 00:43:40,806
My point here is that these visions
are just a snapshotted.

679
00:43:40,931 --> 00:43:42,609
You only see a small portion.

680
00:43:42,734 --> 00:43:45,131
Think of Jesus and his sacrifice.

681
00:43:45,544 --> 00:43:46,824
To his disciples,

682
00:43:46,949 --> 00:43:49,793
it was a tragedy because they couldn't
see the bigger picture.

683
00:43:50,379 --> 00:43:53,593
It's a new reality
for everyone who came after.

684
00:43:54,494 --> 00:43:56,484
Is that what you think
is happening now?

685
00:43:56,609 --> 00:43:59,901
It's not fate versus freewill.

686
00:44:00,185 --> 00:44:01,185
It's fate,

687
00:44:01,826 --> 00:44:02,976
and freewill.

688
00:44:04,702 --> 00:44:07,561
But I'm just a super religious
weirdo dude.

689
00:44:08,245 --> 00:44:10,845
You don't have to believe
anything I say.

690
00:44:11,778 --> 00:44:13,189
But every day,

691
00:44:14,686 --> 00:44:16,946
God puts something good
in your life.

692
00:44:19,216 --> 00:44:21,324
Embrace it.
And let all the other stuff,

693
00:44:22,436 --> 00:44:23,436
fall away.

694
00:44:27,275 --> 00:44:29,332
The challenge we face is recognizing

695
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:31,966
that the answers
to our most burning questions

696
00:44:32,091 --> 00:44:34,452
may be right in front of us.

697
00:44:50,779 --> 00:44:53,274
You sure you don't want to try
our tofurky soy cheesesteak?

698
00:44:53,399 --> 00:44:54,600
It's on special.

699
00:44:54,776 --> 00:44:55,730
I'm positive.

700
00:44:55,855 --> 00:44:59,130
I wish I could have been more help, but
I don't know what you're looking for...

701
00:44:59,255 --> 00:45:00,864
Me neither. Thanks anyway.

702
00:45:01,165 --> 00:45:02,215
No problem.

703
00:45:07,555 --> 00:45:09,331
When did you guys change locations?

704
00:45:09,499 --> 00:45:11,958
About a month ago.
We had a fire during the blackout.

705
00:45:12,243 --> 00:45:15,400
Luckily, I got my money
before the insurance company went broke.

706
00:45:16,234 --> 00:45:18,006
Where was your old location?

707
00:45:23,064 --> 00:45:24,721
How many electron volts
were generated?

708
00:45:25,949 --> 00:45:27,733
It's a number, Dr. Simcoe.

709
00:45:27,963 --> 00:45:29,413
An abstract object.

710
00:45:30,144 --> 00:45:32,294
I can't sacrifice any more lives.

711
00:45:32,584 --> 00:45:34,641
"Sacrifice" is an interesting word.

712
00:45:34,881 --> 00:45:36,274
I appreciate its duality.

713
00:45:36,568 --> 00:45:39,235
It can be used
as either a noun or a verb.

714
00:45:41,322 --> 00:45:42,781
One can take action, surrender,

715
00:45:42,949 --> 00:45:46,076
or give something up
for something else.

716
00:45:46,400 --> 00:45:49,224
- What are you doing?
- I prefer the greek noun form thusia,

717
00:45:49,349 --> 00:45:52,290
to indicate the object itself
that is sacrificed...

718
00:45:52,583 --> 00:45:53,917
Meaning one's family...

719
00:45:54,726 --> 00:45:56,336
or the proverbial pound of flesh.

720
00:46:06,464 --> 00:46:08,515
Tell them what they want, Lloyd!

721
00:46:15,481 --> 00:46:16,669


722
00:46:16,889 --> 00:46:18,317
I'm not saying he's bad.

723
00:46:18,442 --> 00:46:21,149
I just think most religion
is a kind of club

724
00:46:21,274 --> 00:46:24,424
designed to keep some people in
and some people out.

725
00:46:25,678 --> 00:46:28,470
If it makes you feel better ,
what difference does it make?

726
00:46:28,595 --> 00:46:31,162
I'm glad you're feeling better.
I just want you to be careful.

727
00:46:31,830 --> 00:46:32,789
You know what?

728
00:46:32,957 --> 00:46:35,927
Maybe this wasn't the best idea.
Even when her medicine's working,

729
00:46:36,052 --> 00:46:37,847
She's... odd,

730
00:46:37,972 --> 00:46:39,713
And it's unpredictable.

731
00:46:41,169 --> 00:46:42,619
I want to hang out.

732
00:46:42,744 --> 00:46:44,994
So there's nothing to be afraid of.

733
00:46:46,467 --> 00:46:49,467
All right, but if you want to bell,
I totally understand.

734
00:47:02,289 --> 00:47:05,681
Mom, this is my friend Bryce.
We work together at the hospital.

735
00:47:06,154 --> 00:47:08,950
Don't touch my hair.
You'll scare the butterflies away.

736
00:47:10,250 --> 00:47:12,203
So this is the reason
for all the pennies?

737
00:47:15,185 --> 00:47:16,332
You brought pennies?

738
00:47:16,500 --> 00:47:17,834
I got a bunch today.

739
00:47:23,831 --> 00:47:25,048
You're a doctor?

740
00:47:26,039 --> 00:47:27,927
I've been struck by lightning
six times.

741
00:47:34,069 --> 00:47:35,935
Can I help with the wall?

742
00:47:36,937 --> 00:47:39,399
Only use the ones marked 1989.

743
00:47:40,493 --> 00:47:42,493
That's the year
that Nicole was born.

744
00:47:44,183 --> 00:47:45,069
Nice.

745
00:47:45,331 --> 00:47:47,731
This whole thing
is a tribute to her.

746
00:47:49,875 --> 00:47:51,525
You never told me that.

747
00:47:53,794 --> 00:47:55,094
You never asked.

748
00:47:55,219 --> 00:47:56,164
Actually,

749
00:47:56,332 --> 00:47:59,199
we were just discussing a question
that's been bothering us.

750
00:47:59,777 --> 00:48:02,729
Do you think God
caused the flash-forward?

751
00:48:03,203 --> 00:48:04,506
Flash-forward?

